Package: RegCompassR
Title: GRN-First Multiome Reaction and Meta-Module Analysis
Version: 1.8.2
Authors@R: c(person(given = "RegCompass", family = "Developers", role = c("aut", "cre"), email = "dev@example.com"))
Author: RegCompass Developers [aut, cre]
Maintainer: RegCompass Developers <dev@example.com>
Description: Builds condition-by-cell-type regulatory networks from paired
    single-cell RNA and ATAC data, constructs condition-level metacells, maps
    complete-GPR core reactions, expands annotation-defined meta-modules, and
    completes feasible models with FASTCORE. Integrated RNA and ATAC evidence is
    converted to reaction penalties for directional COMPASS-like scoring. A
    post-Layer-2 step can score non-core reactions directly sharing KEGG,
    Reactome, or master-Rhea identifiers with selected cores in the exact global
    union GEM used for the original analysis.
